00:00:40.510 --> 00:00:44.780
We also help our customers
understand their customers providing

00:00:44.780 --> 00:00:48.800
the best possible TV and video solutions.

00:00:48.800 --> 00:00:51.690
The 2012 study was carried out in 
thirteen different

00:00:51.690 --> 00:00:55.440
markets with thirteen thousand
respondents: that's representative for

00:00:55.440 --> 00:01:01.170
475 million consumers.

00:01:01.170 --> 00:01:02.230
First of all,

00:01:02.230 --> 00:01:07.670
the three most important consumer trends is the increase in on-demand, streaming

00:01:07.670 --> 00:01:10.409
and time-shift behaviors among consumers.

00:01:10.409 --> 00:01:14.250
Secondly we can see that social
behavior and how that relates to

00:01:14.250 --> 00:01:18.000
TV and Video - people chatting at the same
time, sharing their

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:23.350
views over social networks.
Third, the companion devices on the second screens

00:01:23.350 --> 00:01:26.880
being able to watch when you want, where
you want also

00:01:26.880 --> 00:01:33.270
and watching on several different screens
at the same time.

00:01:33.270 --> 00:01:35.350
User-experience design

00:01:35.350 --> 00:01:37.500
is the most important part.

00:01:37.500 --> 00:01:42.299
We know that.  We know that they way we
consume whatever service on whatever

00:01:42.299 --> 00:01:44.100
screen we want to have

00:01:44.100 --> 00:01:50.530
a very easily understandable, intuitive, attractive user-experience.

00:01:50.530 --> 00:01:54.200
